ce:section.ce:para:
A comparison of IR spectra of citric acid anhydrous (CA) and GQDs (Fig. S1) presented significant changes in the peak shape and the position. The GQDs spectrum showed board absorption band at 3000–3500cm−1 (νO-H) and sharp absorption bands at 1561cm−1 (νasCOO-), 1379cm−1 (νasCOO-) and 1057cm−1 (νO-H), implying that the GQDs are surrounded by COOH and OH group. The FT-IR spectra (Fig. 3
                        ) of AChE/CHOx and GQDs/AChE/CHOx showed the shift of all peaks. However, the appearance of the additional peak at 1627cm−1 belonging to the characteristic amide peak [29] of AChE/CHOx is indicative of the incorporated GQDs/AChE/CHOx biosensor. Furthermore, the correlated FT-IR spectum of GQDs/AChE/CHOx biosensor in Tris-BSA showed a characteristic amide peak of enzyme and BSA at 1643cm−1 
                        [29,30]. Possibly, these results have been well explained that the enzyme and BSA contain a large globular protein which is rich in amino and carboxyl groups. Thus, the entrapment of GQDs with the enzyme possibly stemmed from the hydrogen bonding and electrostatic interactions of carboxylic groups of the edge of GQDs with amino and carboxyl groups of AChE, CHOx and BSA [9,29–31]. These results clearly indicated the incorporation of enzyme and GQDs in the BSA layer.
